text: {| |} The Fiat A.10 was an Italian 6-cylinder, liquid-cooled, in-line aero engine of World War I. The A.10 was succeeded by the larger A.12. Fiat produced over 15,000 engines during World War I. ==Applications== * Caproni Ca.1 * Caproni Ca.2 * Caproni Ca.32 * SIA 5 ==Specifications (Fiat A.10)== ==See also== ==References== ==Further reading== * A.10 Category:1910s aircraft piston engines
